race.comment: DELAGO LAD (2) led and missed a whisker first-up and then started favourite again and faded out (vet cleared). Inclined to forgive that. Will present fitter and has won 3/5 third up. BAHAMA BAY (3) returns after a spell. Started his last campaign in good style in the placings over 1000m at Darwin. Comes off an easy Darwin win and enjoys this trip. Rates highly. THE GIRL'S BOY (4) raced wide but came home powerfully to score by 1L this trip. Was a comfortable Darwin winner prior and can deliver the hat-trick without surprise. O'TYCOON (1) resumes and would be a contender if presented on song. Races forward and the 2kg claim is handy. KICKATORP (5) tries hard and should be around the mark.
